Refund or credit requests can only be granted when received 48 hours prior to the workshop at the latest. You will have the possibility to manage your registration via the link \"Manage my order\" that you will find in the confirmation e-mail for your registration.\n  Introduction\nA 3.5-hour collaborative workshop to understand as a team\nthe issues faced by our agri-food system\nand discuss on the actions to undertake to address them. \nFor our health, for the environment, for the climate, to preserve the culture of our regions, for more solidarity, we all want sustainable food.\nBut is it that simple? And what does it really imply?\nLet's try and find some answers by participating in The Agri'Food Collage workshop. Directly inspired by The Climate Fresk, The Agri'Food Collage is a scientific and creative workshop designed to acquire as a team an overview of the issues weighing on our food supply, and discuss the actions to be taken to turn it into a solutions platform.\nDeveloped in partnership with ADEME \u2013 the French agency for the ecological transition, The Agri'Food Collage is based on over 150 reference documents and the contribution of experts from the many fields related to our food: environment, economy, society, ... and a bit of history too! See it as the agri-food system \"serious game\", based on collective intelligence and extremely educational because it allows you to learn a lot in a very short time, whether you're just curious or already knowledgeable.\nIt is also an opportunity to meet other people interested in the subject of the sustainability of our food, and to discover an effective tool to raise awareness and catalyze transformative action around you.\nAgenda & Practical Info\n  Workshop language : English.\n  Group introduction\nReconstruction of the Agri'Food Collage\nDebrief\nShare actions ideas\n  Recommended age: 16 and above.\nThis workshop will be held online via videoconference, and we'll be using a web-based visual collaboration tool. Please make sure you have: \na good Internet connection\nuse a computer (no tablets or cell phones) equipped with a microphone (mandatory) and a camera (recommended), and preferably have a wheel mouse at hand. \nAll technical details will be sent to registered participants by e-mail.\nThis session is primarily intended for individuals.\nIf you want to organize a workshop for your teams, we offer dedicated sessions adapted to your needs: contact us!\nTo know more about The Agri'Food Collage\n  Project website\nFollow us on Facebook or LinkedIn\n  You can't make it on that date? And what does it really imply?\nLet's try and find some answers by participating in The Agri'Food Collage workshop. Directly inspired by The Climate Fresk, The Agri'Food Collage is a scientific and creative workshop designed to acquire as a team an overview of the issues weighing on our food supply, and discuss the actions to be taken to turn it into a solutions platform.\nDeveloped in partnership with ADEME \u2013 the French agency for the ecological transition, The Agri'Food Collage is based on over 150 reference documents and the contribution of experts from the many fields related to our food: environment, economy, society, ... and a bit of history too! See it as the agri-food system \"serious game\", based on collective intelligence and extremely educational because it allows you to learn a lot in a very short time, whether you're just curious or already knowledgeable.\nIt is also an opportunity to meet other people interested in the subject of the sustainability of our food, and to discover an effective tool to raise awareness and catalyze transformative action around you.\nAgenda & Practical Info\n  Workshop language : English.\n  Group introduction\nReconstruction of the Agri'Food Collage\nDebrief\nShare actions ideas\n  Recommended age: 16 and above.\nThis workshop will be held online via videoconference, and we'll be using a web-based visual collaboration tool. Please make sure you have: \na good Internet connection\nuse a computer (no tablets or cell phones) equipped with a microphone (mandatory) and a camera (recommended), and preferably have a wheel mouse at hand. \nAll technical details will be sent to registered participants by e-mail.\nThis session is primarily intended for individuals.\nIf you want to organize a workshop for your teams, we offer dedicated sessions adapted to your needs: contact us!\nTo know more about The Agri'Food Collage\n  Project website\nFollow us on Facebook or LinkedIn\n  You can't make it on that date? Bref, l'atelier s'adresse \u00e0 quiconque souhaite comprendre ce qu'il.elle mange ! Aucun pr\u00e9requis n'est demand\u00e9 pour faire l'atelier !\nD\u00e9roul\u00e9\nL\u2019atelier dure 3h et se d\u00e9coupe en plusieurs \u00e9tapes :\nD\u00e9marrage (30 min) : icebreaker, pr\u00e9sentation des participant.e.s, de l\u2019animateur.rice, de l\u2019atelier, \u2026\nR\u00e9flexion (1h15) : \u00e9tude des causes et cons\u00e9quences de nos consommations sur le climat, la biodiversit\u00e9, la sant\u00e9 et la r\u00e9silience alimentaire\nSolutions (30 min) : quelles solutions pouvons-nous mettre en place d\u00e8s maintenant \u00e0 notre \u00e9chelle pour tendre vers une alimentation plus durable ? Quelles sont leurs cons\u00e9quences ?\nActions (30 min) : choix d\u2019une action individuelle et une action collective pour tendre vers une alimentation plus durable et anticipation des difficult\u00e9s/freins qui pourraient \u00eatre rencontr\u00e9s\nD\u00e9brief (15 min) : retours sur l\u2019atelier, derniers conseils, quelle suite donner \u00e0 l\u2019atelier, ...\nCroyez-nous, \u00e7a passe (tr\u00e8s) vite !\nInfos pratiques\nMat\u00e9riel\nVous n'avez besoin de rien ! :)\nVous voulez organiser un atelier pour votre structure?\nhttps://forms.gle/ZhiyKGgcQmMYQxMt7\n  Contacts\nSite internet : http://fresquealimentation.org\nPage LinkedIn\nPage Facebook\n  A bient\u00f4t ;)",

Quelles sont leurs cons\u00e9quences ?\nActions (30 min) : choix d\u2019une action individuelle et une action collective pour tendre vers une alimentation plus durable et anticipation des difficult\u00e9s/freins qui pourraient \u00eatre rencontr\u00e9s\nD\u00e9brief (15 min) : retours sur l\u2019atelier, derniers conseils, quelle suite donner \u00e0 l\u2019atelier, ...\nCroyez-nous, \u00e7a passe (tr\u00e8s) vite !\nInfos pratiques\nMat\u00e9riel\nVous aurez simplement besoin d\u2019un ordinateur, d\u2019un micro et d\u2019une connexion internet suffisante pour pouvoir \u00e9changer avec les autres participant.e.s. Aucun pr\u00e9requis n'est demand\u00e9 pour faire l'atelier !\nL'atelier sera anim\u00e9 par Thomas Moulin co-auteur de La Fresque de l'Alimentation.\nD\u00e9roul\u00e9\nL\u2019atelier dure 3h et se d\u00e9coupe en plusieurs \u00e9tapes :\nD\u00e9marrage (30 min) : icebreaker, pr\u00e9sentation des participant.e.s, de l\u2019animateur.rice, de l\u2019atelier, \u2026\nR\u00e9flexion (1h15) : \u00e9tude des causes et cons\u00e9quences de nos consommations sur le climat, la biodiversit\u00e9, la sant\u00e9 et la r\u00e9silience alimentaire\nSolutions (30 min) : quelles solutions pouvons-nous mettre en place d\u00e8s maintenant \u00e0 notre \u00e9chelle pour tendre vers une alimentation plus durable ? Quelles sont leurs cons\u00e9quences ?\nActions (30 min) : choix d\u2019une action individuelle et une action collective pour tendre vers une alimentation plus durable et anticipation des difficult\u00e9s/freins qui pourraient \u00eatre rencontr\u00e9s\nD\u00e9brief (15 min) : retours sur l\u2019atelier, derniers conseils, quelle suite donner \u00e0 l\u2019atelier, ...\nCroyez-nous, \u00e7a passe (tr\u00e8s) vite !\nInfos pratiques\nMat\u00e9riel\nVous n'avez besoin de rien ! :)\n\nVous n'\u00eates pas dispo sur les dates existantes ?     "description": "- L\u2019association et le jeu\nLa Fresque de la Construction est un atelier ludique et collaboratif de 3 heures sur le th\u00e8me de la construction pour r\u00e9pondre aux enjeux du changement climatique.\n\nLe jeu est inspir\u00e9 de la Fresque du Climat et propos\u00e9 par l\u2019association de loi 1901 La Fresque de la Construction, une organisation non gouvernementale, \u00e0 but non lucratif, cr\u00e9\u00e9e le 17 f\u00e9vrier 2021. Cette association regroupe en France, une cinquantaine de membres et plus de 200 animateurs et animatrices.\n\nLe jeu se d\u00e9cline en 45 cartes de jeu et 60 cartes de strat\u00e9gies d'action.\nCet atelier offre une approche ludique pour appr\u00e9hender les enjeux associ\u00e9s au secteur \u00e0 travers cinq th\u00e9matiques cl\u00e9s et leurs cons\u00e9quences : les besoins, l\u2019urbanisme, la conception, la construction, l\u2019usage.\n  - D\u00e9roul\u00e9 de l\u2019atelier\nL\u2019atelier dure 3 heures et se d\u00e9roule en trois phases :\n1. Compr\u00e9hension : d\u00e9couvrir les cartes et co-construire la fresque \n2. Cr\u00e9ativit\u00e9 : d\u00e9briefer en \u00e9quipe et personnaliser la fresque\n3. Pistes d\u2019action : explorer les axes de r\u00e9flexion, imaginer des actions et d\u00e9battre en groupe\n  - A qui s\u2019adresse l\u2019atelier ?\nLes ateliers publics s'adressent \u00e0 toute personne qui s\u2019int\u00e9resse au secteur de la construction et \u00e0 son impact sur l\u2019environnement. Ils sont organis\u00e9s par des b\u00e9n\u00e9voles. Jusqu'\u00e0 2 repr\u00e9sentants par entreprise peuvent participer \u00e0 un atelier.\n\nPour organiser un atelier d\u00e9di\u00e9 \u00e0 votre \u00e9quipe ou entreprise, contactez directement l'association ou renseignez le formulaire dans le lien ci-apr\u00e8s : FDLC - demande d'atelier intraentreprise\n  - Conditions d\u2019annulation et de remboursement\n  Annulation par le participant : remboursement si l\u2019annulation est effectu\u00e9e jusqu'\u00e0 48 heures avant l'\u00e9v\u00e9nement. \nLes frais de la billetterie ne sont pas remboursables.\n  Annulation par l\u2019association : la Fresque de la Construction peut \u00eatre amen\u00e9e \u00e0 annuler une session si le nombre minimum de participants souhait\u00e9 n\u2019est pas atteint.\nDans ce cas l\u2019association remboursera le billet dans sa totalit\u00e9.",

Cette association regroupe en France, une cinquantaine de membres et plus de 200 animateurs et animatrices.\n\nLe jeu se d\u00e9cline en 45 cartes de jeu et 60 cartes de strat\u00e9gies d'action.\nCet atelier offre une approche ludique pour appr\u00e9hender les enjeux associ\u00e9s au secteur \u00e0 travers cinq th\u00e9matiques cl\u00e9s et leurs cons\u00e9quences : les besoins, l\u2019urbanisme, la conception, la construction, l\u2019usage.\n  - D\u00e9roul\u00e9 de l\u2019atelier\nL\u2019atelier dure 3 heures et se d\u00e9roule en trois phases :\n1. Ils sont organis\u00e9s par des b\u00e9n\u00e9voles. Les cartes, intuitives et visuelles, permettent en peu de temps de d\u00e9couvrir les ordres de grandeur li\u00e9s aux r\u00e9alit\u00e9s du quotidien (alimentation, transport, logement\u2026).\nL'atelier nous montre qu\u2019on peut vivre mieux en r\u00e9pondant \u00e0 l\u2019urgence climatique. Il nous aide \u00e0 comprendre pour agir efficacement et nous am\u00e8ne \u00e0 changer de regard sur ce qui compte vraiment.\nL'atelier se d\u00e9roule en deux temps. Le premier pour prendre conscience de la situation climatique actuelle. Le deuxi\u00e8me pour inventer des vies sobres et heureuses, compatibles avec les enjeux environnementaux visant la neutralit\u00e9 carbone.\n  IMPORTANT : le lieu met la salle \u00e0 disposition \u00e0 condition de prendre un gouter \u00e0 7\u20ac.     "description": "10 am to 1 pm Tokyo time\n  Check for the time in your location :\nEvent Time Announcer - Textiles Untangled online workshop\n    Facilitators: Sakura HAMAOKA & Lavanya JAYAKAR\n  Textiles are everywhere! In our clothing, furniture, toys and even computers! But how much do you really know about them? What exactly are our textiles made from? How sustainable are they, really? How far do our clothes travel before we buy them? Where do they go once they are donated?\n  This collaborative workshop illustrates the complexities and impacts (social and ecological) of the textile industry by using clothing as a case study. You will create the production chain of textiles, learn about the industry\u2019s impact, and then work together to find solutions and actions you can take.\n  This workshop is inspired by the pedagogy of the Climate Fresk (an interactive workshop that teaches the IPCC Climate report). Experience this unique way of learning, if you are new to the Fresk universe of workshops. Launched in 2021, Textiles UnTangled has been enjoyed by over 600 participants.\n  You will learn:\n  1. Materials 101 - What fabrics should I choose!?!\n2. The life cycle of textiles, from raw materials to end of life\n3. Textile industry impacts on the planet and on humans.\n4. How to think critically of claims made by companies & organizations about their sustainability\n5. Notions of circular economy, systems view thinking, and human centered solutions\n6. Actions that can be taken on a collective, business, and individual level\nAll while working together and having fun!\n  Our main sources: Ellen MacArthur Foundation, Preferred Textiles Report, OXFAM, Fashion Revolution and ADEME.\n  What participants have said:\n  \"This game is a fun, civic-minded and inclusive way to think about our relationship to clothing. I highly recommend it!\" - Anonymous\n  \"I learned valuable information about the choices one can make to minimize one's impact of GHGs and other pollutants when consuming textiles, whether it be clothing, furniture or other textile products.\" - Alex\n  A nice workshop to better understand the impacts of the textile industry with lots of mini games. Fun and interesting, for everyone, I love it! - Sylvaine\n  Thank you to them and all our participants! We have a 4.4 / 5 satisfaction rate!\n  Who is this for?\n  All expertise levels welcome! From people who wear clothing (haha) to textile producers! Textiles are everywhere and concern everyone. Experts in the field also enjoy this workshop and its ability to give a holistic view of the industry, spark discussion, and capacity-build in their organizations. Some companies who have played: Vestiaire Collective, Deloitte, Givenchy, Promod, Caroll and Minelli, Balzac, and Electrolux. For a private session you can contact: greendonut.info@gmail.com\n  Who is this by?\n  Textiles UnTangled game workshop (Textile Collage) was created by the volunteers at Green Donut. Created in France in 2019, Green Donut is an association whose mission is to promote the donut economics model by Kate Raworth (a society prospering within environmental and social limits) via their serious games and actions in the community. They are professionals, experts and concerned citizens of many backgrounds. While based in France, they have diverse backgrounds and welcome members from other countries.\n  Their website (in french only for now) with all their events including our Fresque de D\u00e9chets (Waste Collage = French only): http://greendonut.org\n  Commitment and Cancellation\n  This workshop is a small group workshop (max 8 participants) that needs a minimum to fully capitalise on our collective intelligence. If you must cancel, please do so a week before. Request a refund via Billetweb and it will be granted, minus the Evenbrite fees. If cancelled within a week, please let us know. You are welcome to transfer the ticket to someone else. You can notify us at greendonut.info@gmail.com. Thanks in advance.\n    Now let\u2019s learn about textiles to change the world together!\n   ",

Vous avez 3 heures et 50 leviers pour imaginer un quartier d\u00e9carbon\u00e9, r\u00e9silient et agr\u00e9able \u00e0 vivre !\n  Face \u00e0 l\u2019urgence climatique, comment agir dans les domaines de l\u2019am\u00e9nagement et de la construction ?\nFaut-il v\u00e9g\u00e9taliser les toitures ou r\u00e9nover les b\u00e2timents existants ? Pi\u00e9tonniser les rues ou investir dans des syst\u00e8mes de smart city ? Construire en b\u00e9ton bas carbone ou privil\u00e9gier le r\u00e9emploi des mat\u00e9riaux ? Vous incarnez les r\u00f4les d'am\u00e9nageur, \u00e9lu ou citoyen, et prenez ces d\u00e9cisions ensemble.\n\nVos choix sont imm\u00e9diatement \u00e9valu\u00e9s avec des r\u00e9sultats quantifi\u00e9s bas\u00e9s sur des donn\u00e9es reconnues.     "description": "The Circular Economy Collage will give you a clearer understanding of the issues related to our use of natural resources and to the waste we generate.\n  Which resources do we consume the most and which are most under pressure? What impacts do our consumption and waste generation have on those resources and on the planet in general?\nHow can I contribute to reducing those impacts in my daily life? How can companies evolve their business models?\nTo discover the answers to these and many other questions, come and take part in a workshop of the Circular Economy Collage. The workshop covers topics such as climate change, biodiversity loss, resource scarcity and pollution generated by human activities and enables you to identify concrete courses of action!\nAbout the workshop\nThe Circular Economy Collage is a stimulating, group-based workshop founded on scientific information, which enables participants to grasp the limits of our existing global \u201clinear\u201d economy and understand the opportunities offered by the circular economy. Inspired by the Climate Fresk, the workshop will allow you to understand the issues surrounding our use of natural resources and our generation and treatment of waste as well as other impacts caused by human activities. The workshop lasts 3 hours and takes place in groups of 6/7 people with 1 facilitator.\nThe Circular Economy Collage workshops are aimed at the general public, and are open to all, whatever your level of knowledge on these subjects. The Collage is also relevant for other audiences such as companies, communities and schools.  For our public workshops, participation is limited to 1 participant per organisation. If several members of your organisation wish to take part, please contact us to organise a dedicated session.\nBenefits of the workshop\nHaving deepened your understanding of the limits of the linear production-consumption-waste system, you will discover a more virtuous model for our economy and lots of ways that each of us can save natural resources and produce less waste. You will leave the workshop more aware, better-informed and motivated to take action to \"circularise\" our system!",

    "description": "The Circular Economy Collage will give you a clearer understanding of the issues related to our use of natural resources and to the waste we generate.\n  Which resources do we consume the most and which are most under pressure? What impacts do our consumption and waste generation have on those resources and on the planet in general?\nHow can I contribute to reducing those impacts in my daily life? How can companies evolve their business models?\nTo discover the answers to these and many other questions, come and take part in a workshop of the Circular Economy Collage. The workshop covers topics such as climate change, biodiversity loss, resource scarcity and pollution generated by human activities and enables you to identify concrete courses of action!\nAbout the workshop\nThe Circular Economy Collage is a stimulating, group-based workshop founded on scientific information, which enables participants to grasp the limits of our existing global \u201clinear\u201d economy and understand the opportunities offered by the circular economy. Inspired by the Climate Fresk, the workshop will allow you to understand the issues surrounding our use of natural resources and our generation and treatment of waste as well as other impacts caused by human activities. The workshop lasts 3 hours and takes place in groups of 6/7 people with 1 facilitator.\nThe Circular Economy Collage workshops are aimed at the general public, and are open to all, whatever your level of knowledge on these subjects. The Collage is also relevant for other audiences such as companies, communities and schools.  For our public workshops, participation is limited to 1 participant per organisation. If several members of your organisation wish to take part, please contact us to organise a dedicated session.\nBenefits of the workshop\nHaving deepened your understanding of the limits of the linear production-consumption-waste system, you will discover a more virtuous model for our economy and lots of ways that each of us can save natural resources and produce less waste. You will leave the workshop more aware, better-informed and motivated to take action to \"circularise\" our system!",

What impacts do our consumption and waste generation have on those resources and on the planet in general?\nHow can I contribute to reducing those impacts in my daily life? How can companies evolve their business models?\nTo discover the answers to these and many other questions, come and take part in a workshop of the Circular Economy Collage. The workshop covers topics such as climate change, biodiversity loss, resource scarcity and pollution generated by human activities and enables you to identify concrete courses of action!\nAbout the workshop\nThe Circular Economy Collage is a stimulating, group-based workshop founded on scientific information, which enables participants to grasp the limits of our existing global \u201clinear\u201d economy and understand the opportunities offered by the circular economy. Inspired by the Climate Fresk, the workshop will allow you to understand the issues surrounding our use of natural resources and our generation and treatment of waste as well as other impacts caused by human activities. The workshop lasts 3 hours and takes place in groups of 6/7 people with 1 facilitator.\nThe Circular Economy Collage workshops are aimed at the general public, and are open to all, whatever your level of knowledge on these subjects. The Collage is also relevant for other audiences such as companies, communities and schools.  For our public workshops, participation is limited to 1 participant per organisation. If several members of your organisation wish to take part, please contact us to organise a dedicated session.\nBenefits of the workshop\nHaving deepened your understanding of the limits of the linear production-consumption-waste system, you will discover a more virtuous model for our economy and lots of ways that each of us can save natural resources and produce less waste. You will leave the workshop more aware, better-informed and motivated to take action to \"circularise\" our system!",

Inspired by the Climate Fresk, the workshop will allow you to understand the issues surrounding our use of natural resources and our generation and treatment of waste as well as other impacts caused by human activities. If several members of your organisation wish to take part, please contact us to organise a dedicated session.\nBenefits of the workshop\nHaving deepened your understanding of the limits of the linear production-consumption-waste system, you will discover a more virtuous model for our economy and lots of ways that each of us can save natural resources and produce less waste. You will leave the workshop more aware, better-informed and motivated to take action to \"circularise\" our system!",

    "description": "Description\nD\u00e9couvrez la version am\u00e9lior\u00e9e de La Fresque du Climat qui propose un nouvel \u00e9quilibre entre science, \u00e9motions et action, pour mieux comprendre, explorer des solutions et raviver l'envie d'agir.\n\nLa Fresque du Climat est un atelier cr\u00e9atif et p\u00e9dagogique qui se d\u00e9roule en petits groupes de 5, 6 ou 7 participants autour d'une table. Adress\u00e9 aussi bien aux novices qu\u2019aux connaisseurs (\u00e0 partir de 16 ans), le jeu se compose de 42 cartes avec une image au recto et des explications au verso. \nL'intelligence collective permet de recomposer l'ensemble des liens de cause \u00e0 effet entre les activit\u00e9s humaines et leurs cons\u00e9quences tandis que l'animateur vous accompagne et apporte quelques explications compl\u00e9mentaires. \nEn 3 heures, on acc\u00e8de aux \u00e9l\u00e9ments essentiels des publications scientifiques synth\u00e9tis\u00e9es par le GIEC dans ses rapports et on prend la mesure des ordres de grandeurs \u00e0 la fois mondiaux et locaux. \nCette aide \u00e0 la d\u00e9cision participe \u00e0 augmenter la pertinence de nos choix, et donne du punch \u00e0 notre inventivit\u00e9. \nD\u00e9roul\u00e9 1h30 - REFLEXION : Co-construire la Fresque en 5 \u00e9tapes \n0h30 - CR\u00c9ATIVIT\u00c9 : D\u00e9compresser, s\u2019approprier la fresque en l'illustrant et se nourrir des compl\u00e9mentarit\u00e9s en \u00e9quipe. \n1h \u2013 DEBRIEF : Echanger sur ses \u00e9motions et questionnements, puis \u00e9baucher de pistes d'actions individuelles ou collectives, citoyennes ou professionnelles. \nInfos pratiques \u2022 Inscription obligatoire en ligne (une personne/commande) \u2022 \nMerci d'arriver 5-10 minutes en avance pour commencer et terminer \u00e0 l'heure. \u2022 \nContact : Elise Reynier, e.reynier@venelles.fr \u2022 \nPour cet atelier, les animateurs interviennent \u00e0 titre b\u00e9n\u00e9vole en tant que membres actifs de l\u2019association.     "description": "Description\nVenez comprendre les enjeux climatiques dans cet atelier d'intelligence collective.\n\nL'atelier La Fresque du Climat est un outil p\u00e9dagogique permettant de comprendre rapidement les causes et les effets du changement climatique. Il est destin\u00e9 aussi bien aux novices qu'aux connaisseurs (\u00e0 partir de 16 ans environ). Pendant 3h, l'atelier rassemble les participants par groupes de 5 \u00e0 6 personnes autour d'une table. Le jeu s'articule autour d'un jeu de 42 cartes, il fait appel \u00e0 la cr\u00e9ativit\u00e9 et \u00e0 l'intelligence collective du groupe pour reconstituer les liens de cause \u00e0 effet des cartes propos\u00e9es. Un animateur sera l\u00e0 pour vous guider et pourra vous apporter des explications compl\u00e9mentaires si besoin.\n\nPlus pr\u00e9cis\u00e9ment, nous passerons 3h ensemble :\n R\u00e9flexion (1h30) : d\u00e9couvrir et mettre en lien les cartes pour co-construire la fresque.\n Cr\u00e9ativit\u00e9 (30min) : d\u00e9compresser, s\u2019approprier la fresque et cr\u00e9er un esprit d\u2019\u00e9quipe en l\u2019illustrant.\n Debrief (1h) : \u00e9changer sur ses \u00e9motions, questions, et r\u00e9fl\u00e9chir collectivement aux solutions individuelles et collectives. \n\nMerci d'arriver 10 minutes en avance pour commencer et terminer \u00e0 l\u2019heure.\n\n- Nombre de places : 2 tables (12 personnes)\n- Contact : Benjamin Meriaux, b.meriaux@ca-pso.fr, 06.38.10.94.01",
